NEW YORK — Yes, it’s only mid-June. But with the Yankees off to a historic 44-16 start and holding a nine-game lead, the Rays can’t make up ground soon enough. They will have that opportunity in their hands over much of the next week and a half, playing them three times at Yankee Stadium starting tonight, then three more starting Monday at Tropicana Field. The Yankees’ starting pitching has been extremely good and very challenging this season, and the Rays will see three good ones this series, starting with Gerrit Cole tonight. They do have the benefit of having Ji-Man Choi, who has had extraordinary success against Cole, in their lineup, hitting cleanup. The Rays are starting veteran Corey Kluber, who held the Yankees to one run over six innings in his May 28 outing. Here is the Rays lineup: And for the Yankees, without Josh Donaldson, whose suspension was upheld: • • • Sign up for the Rays Report weekly newsletter to get fresh perspectives on the Tampa Bay Rays and the rest of the majors from sports columnist John Romano. Never miss out on the latest with the Bucs, Rays, Lightning, Florida college sports and more. Follow our Tampa Bay Times sports team on Twitter and Facebook.